drjoliv.fjava.monad

Interface Monad<M extends Witness,A>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Applicative<M,A>, Functor<M,A>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Either.LeftProjection, Either.RightProjection, Eval, FList, FList.Cons, FList.Nil, Identity, Maybe, Maybe.Just, Maybe.None, MaybeT, ReaderT, ReaderT.Reader, StateT, StateT.State, Trampoline, Try, Try.TryT, WriterT, WriterT.Writer

    public interface Monad<M extends Witness,A>
extends Applicative<M,A>
    A computation that can be chain with other computations. Each monad determins how computaions are chained allowing for unique sidee effects for different monads when chaining computaitons.
    Author:
    Desonte 'drjoliv' Jolivet : drjoliv@gmail.com
